<item>
            <title>[LU-3854] Lustre 1.8.9 misconfigures the o2ib LND driver.</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3854</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This bug is similar to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2631&quot; title=&quot;build fails on 2.6.18-348.el5 with o2ib&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2631&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-2631&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; in that the vlan_dev_vlan_id change in the RHEL5 2.6.18-348.el5 causes some OFED configuration test to fail when they should succeed. The solution is also similar in that that we update the OFED&lt;br/&gt;
configuration test to use fc_compat.h when needed. Oops happen when o2ib LND driver is misconfigured.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Any system with inifiniband hardware running RHEL5 with Lustre 1.8.9 software.</environment>
        <key id="20673">LU-3854</key>
